Get started by installing the plugin and then running:

rake casein:fast_setup email=your@email.com
(change the email to whatever you want)

rails g casein_scaffold Article title:string body:text --create-model-and-migration
(change the model name and attributes)

-- the Ã¼ber fast way to get started --

Granted you have the usual suspects installed, just run this to get a quick test up going:

rails fresh-casein-app && cd fresh-casein-app && rails plugin install git@github.com:spoiledmilk/casein3.git && rake casein:fast_setup email=my@email.com && rails g casein_scaffold Article title:string body:text --create-model-and-migration && rake db:migrate && rails server

Now, go to: http://localhost:3000/casein/articles


